The paper investigates the similarities of pairs of articles based on co-citation levels, which is a common topic in information retrieval (cs.IR) and digital libraries (cs.DL). The analysis involves measuring textual similarity, which is a key aspect of natural language processing (cs.CL). The study also involves the comparison of different journals, which could fall under the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI) or cybernetics (cs.CY).
